Labels in HTML are used to describe or identify input fields, making forms more user-friendly and accessible. 
The <label> tag is paired with an input using the for attribute, which matches the input's id.

<label for="username">Username:</label>
<input type="text" id="username" name="username">

when in the ouput if you see when you click on the username you automatically clicked the input field as well so it is basicallay a better way to use in the forms 
the more you will see in the project 
